headline.main: DISCOVERER CAPSULE FAILS TO GO IN ORBIT

results.snippet: VANDENBERG AIR FORCE BASE, Calif., March 30 (UPI) -- The Air Force failed today to orbit a Discoverer Satellite with a recoverable capsule carrying living tissue to gauge cosmic radiation that might face the first United States astronaut.
